cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with the problem of building footprint generation from remote sensing imagery using convolution neural network (CNN) and graph model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel graph model called feature pairwise conditional random field (FPCRF), which takes spatial correlation into consideration and preserves sharp boundaries and fine-grained segmentation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with remote sensing data, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
